"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"     * Framingham risk scoring system for men. Use to calculate the risk of developing clinical coronary heart disease (CHD) in men who do not have known CHD. Clinical CHD includes angina pectoris, recognized or unrecognized myocardial infarction (MI), coronary insufficiency (prolonged chest discomfort associated with transient repolarization abnormalities without criteria for MI), or CHD death.",
"     <br>",
"      To calculate the Framingham risk estimate, add points for age, presence of diabetes, smoking status, LDL-cholesterol (LDL-C), HDL-cholesterol (HDL-C), and blood pressure. Find the total point score on the bottom table to determine the 10-year risk of CHD.",
"     </br>",
"    </div>",
